  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, a standalone mining client (e.g. ethminer) must poll geth to check for new work.  The polling interval can be reduced (e.g. ethminer --farm-recheck 200), but this increases the load on the geth server.\n\nIf the geth server could notify the mining clients when new work is available, it would reduce the load on the geth server and reduce the amount of time mining clients are hashing on old work.\n\nOne possible implementation is to provide a second version of the eth_getWork RPC call which doesn't return until either new work is available or a timeout is reached.\n",
